  "prompt": "What is the best Pre & Post Workout meals?",
  "response": "The best pre- and post-workout meals optimize energy, performance, and recovery. Here\u2019s a breakdown of what to eat **before** and **after** your workout based on your goals and the type of exercise:\n\n---\n\n### **Pre-Workout Meal (1-3 hours before exercise)**  \nThe goal is to fuel your body with energy and improve performance. Focus on **carbohydrates** for quick energy, **protein** for muscle support, and **minimal fat** (to avoid digestion issues).  \n\n**Timing:**  \n- **If eating 2-3 hours before:** A balanced meal with carbs, protein, and a small amount of fat.  \n- **If eating 30-60 minutes before:** A light snack focusing on carbs and a bit of protein.  \n\n**Examples:**  \n1. **2-3 Hours Before:**  \n   - Grilled chicken + quinoa + steamed veggies  \n   - Oatmeal with banana and a scoop of almond butter  \n   - Whole-grain toast + avocado + a boiled egg  \n\n2. **30-60 Minutes Before:**  \n   - Greek yogurt with berries  \n   - A banana with a handful of nuts  \n   - A small protein smoothie with fruit  \n\n**Key Nutrients:**  \n- **Carbs:** Oats, rice, fruit, whole-grain bread  \n- **Protein:** Greek yogurt, eggs, chicken, protein powder  \n- **Fats:** Small amounts of nut butter, avocado, or olive oil  \n\n---\n\n### **Post-Workout Meal (within 30-60 minutes after exercise)**  \nThe goal is to replenish glycogen stores, repair muscle tissue, and rehydrate. Focus on **protein** for muscle recovery and **carbs** to restore energy.  \n\n**Examples:**  \n1. Grilled salmon + sweet potatoes + broccoli  \n2. Protein shake with a banana or berries  \n3. Scrambled eggs + spinach + whole-grain toast  \n4. Chicken wrap with quinoa, veggies, and hummus  \n\n**Key Nutrients:**  \n- **Protein:** Lean meats, fish, eggs, tofu, protein powder (20-30g is ideal)  \n- **Carbs:** Rice, potatoes, fruit, whole grains  \n- **Healthy Fats:** Avocado, nuts, seeds (in moderation)  \n- **Hydration:** Water or an electrolyte drink  \n\n---\n\n### **Additional Tips:**  \n- **Hydration is key:** Drink water before, during, and after your workout.  \n- **Tailor to your workout:**  \n  - For **endurance training**, prioritize more carbs.  \n  - For **strength training**, focus on protein and carbs.  \n- **Listen to your body:** Adjust portion sizes and timing based on how your body responds.  \n\nBy planning your pre- and post-workout meals, you\u2019ll optimize your energy, performance, and recovery!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
